  "riddle": "1. Unearth the gathering place where neighbors unite in Skeldon, a town nestled in South America. What country welcomes this hub of community spirit?\n\n2. Upon reaching this locale, how high do the grounds rise above sea level in Guyana?\n\n3. Your journey continues; seek out how many parks flourish within proximity to this town of Skeldon.\n\n4. Combine the elevation you uncovered about Skeldon with the count of nearby parks. What new number emerges from your addition?\n\n5. In the realm of cricket, there lies a team that represents a country. What capacity awaits spectators at their grand home ground?\n\n6. Flip the digits of that capacity number – what fresh value do you discover in this reversal?\n\n7. Turn your attention now to the population of the proud land that boasts a cricketing legacy.\n\n8. From the cricket fields to the heart of competition, what is the population of this same country again? \n\n9. Observe carefully: how many '1' bits dance within the binary frame of the number you found in clue 8? \n\n10. Backtrack to the world of cricket and find yet again the population of this country. \n\n11. Count how many fellows reside in this land once more – what is the figure?\n\n12. Conclude your quest by computing the remainder of (clue 4 + clue 6 + clue 9) when divided by 10. This final result will reveal a single digit, where will your journey's number lie?",
